## Verification checklist

- Gameplay random uses only `SeededRandom` and `SeededPicker`.
- `cyrb53 + mulberry32` remains stable.
- All gameplay random consumes unified `state["random"]`.
- Every random-consuming API returns updated random state.
- Step counts match the PRD exactly.
- Tags are labels only.
- Active previews and selectors do not mutate active random.
- Contract setup preview uses only temporary setup random.
- Allowed consumers list was not expanded without PRD approval.
- `WinnerResolver` and documented deterministic tie-breaks use no random.
- Visual-only RNG cannot affect state, logs, replay, or gameplay decisions.
- Static scans cover forbidden random APIs.
- Replay tests and exact step assertions cover random changes.
